<br>
3. Clerics that don't have heal messages. I mean how hard is it to make a hot button that gives the message every time you hit your heal hot button? I have played a cleric to level 33, I know its not that hard. Just make one or I am gonna go evasive to save my own arse every time you don't bother to use it!<br>
<br>
4. Clerics that heal at like 60% of my health. I may not have the 8500 hps buffed that other tanks have, but your wasting mana not letting me use all that I do have. Unless the mob is hitting for 900 hps a pop (in wich case we probably have more than one healer on me and its a raid) let me go beserk every now and again. Especially if you have a heal message.<br>
<br>
5. People that make me pull. I don't mind pulling when there is no one else equally suited for the job. Afterall, if I have the hps why not. But, when there is someone who can harmony split or fd, they should be pulling cause otherwise the pulls will be slow or we will have trains... your choice.<br>
<br>
6. People who say &quot;oh you should just go get xyz weapon or gear and your problems will be all gone&quot;. If I can buy it from a vendor, I would have it already, If it were easy to obtain I would have it already. <br>
<br>
7. Casters who complain that they have to kill mobs with an exp group to get their spell upgrades. <br>
