<br>
1. No load pussnuts that train the graveyards in PoP. If you do something stupid, suck it up and die. Your corpse will pop in 15 min or so and you can get a rez there. There are people trying to loot in the gy's...or just zone in. They shouldn't have to deal with your whining maggot antics because you can't have the courtesy to deal with a mistake.<br>
<br>
2. Cockbreath monks that come to a warrior gripe board and bitch that the mitigation they shouldn't have had in the first place got dialed back to a more appropriate level. You got a problem with your class, bitch on your own cess pit board.<br>
<br>
3. People on raids who are pathologically incapable of waiting for an assist message, with a secondary gripe for those who cant' follow directions. It never fails. No matter how many times you say it in channel, there's always some mensa member who attacks before you call assist. No matter how many times you tell people to attack at max melee or from behind the mob, there's always some brain trust standing in front of you.<br>
<br>
4. Anyone who tells me how to play my character. It's mine. I play it my way. I'm considered pretty good at it by people who's opinion I value, so either shut the f*ck up or get another warrior for your group.<br>
<br>
5. Anyone who has no concept of agro management. Not the monk who fd's and gets agro the second he stands up...he's doing it right. But the monk with the high agro weapons and ungodly speed who forgets he has fd, or the rogue who doesn't know how to evade and insists on using a wavecrasher in his offhand. Pick your class...there's bad examples in each one.<br>
<br>
6. Enrage. I hate enrage and the fact that almost every mob in PoP has it. It's totally killed the social aspect of the game. You can't, especially in a fast paced group, look up for even a second from the window your enrage message goes to. Forget about chatting with the group members or watching what's going on in guild. Forget looking up to see what your kid is yelling about. You do, you die. I hate that it makes me look like a prick because I never talk in group because I'm trying to pay attention so the group doesn't have to stop and rez me ever other mob.<br>
<br>
7. Big steps in every elemental zone. I have to be shrunk on raids...everyone except for short races does on our raids, it's policy. Makes it easier to get more people in to the mob and lets the two or three people who don't get shrunk see what's going on better. We kill the mob...and then move...and I spend either 10 min trying to get up the stairs, or have to get a lev which causes lag. <br>
<br>
8. Allakhazam posters who say &quot;by such and such level you'll have something better than this, so it's obviously a monk/bard/treehugger item&quot;  <br>
<br>
*edit*<br>
9. Idiots, usually monks, that feel the need to run around in a circle for hours on end. Doubly so if they do it around me.<br>
<br>
i'm sure i'll think of more, but that will do for now.<br>
<br>
peace,<br>
Aielman KajiraLiege<br>
